Traffic Anomaly Detection System

Real-time monitoring and analysis for safer roads and efficient traffic management.

Live Traffic Monitoring

Continuously monitor traffic flow and detect anomalies such as wrong-way driving and prohibited area violations.

Recorded Footage Analysis

Upload and analyze recorded video footage to identify traffic incidents and improve safety measures.

Customizable Detection Models

Choose from multiple detection models or customize your own to suit specific traffic monitoring needs.

Problem Domain

The primary challenge in traffic surveillance is to detect and respond to anomalous behavior in real time. These anomalies may include wrong-way driving, over-speeding, illegal lane changes, unauthorized entry into prohibited zones, or pedestrians walking off the footpath. Additionally, emergency vehicles such as ambulances, fire trucks, and police cars must be identified and prioritized while ensuring that normal traffic rules are not incorrectly applied to them.

Manual traffic monitoring systems are often unable to consistently detect such events due to human limitations, making automated systems a more reliable and scalable alternative.

Problem Statement

  • Detect traffic violations such as wrong-way driving, footpath misuse, prohibited area entry, over-speeding, and unsafe lane changes.
  • Track vehicles and pedestrians in real time and monitor their movement patterns.
  • Detect accidents through both visual evidence and trajectory-based collision prediction.
  • Identify emergency vehicles and exempt them from specific rules.
  • Provide a user-friendly interface for uploading and analyzing traffic videos.

Objectives

  • Develop a system that detects various traffic anomalies using computer vision and deep learning.
  • Implement object detection using a YOLOv10s model trained on real-world traffic scenarios.
  • Track detected objects using Kalman filters and analyze their movement.
  • Identify emergency vehicles and ensure rule exceptions are applied where applicable.
  • Detect accidents using a dual approach: visual (pre-trained model) and trajectory-based.
  • Design a frontend dashboard for reviewing detection results and violations.

Scope of the Project

  • Object detection for vehicles, persons, helmets, and emergency vehicles.
  • Violation detection including wrong-way driving, and prohibited area entry.
  • Accident detection using both trajectory collision and visual models.
  • Rule exemption for emergency vehicles (e.g., allowing wrong-way driving).
  • A user interface to upload video and view results with visual annotations.
  • Currently supports video file inputs and designed for future real-time stream integration.
